        <argsstring>)(void *priv)</argsstring>
        <name>unbound</name>
        <qualifiedname>ipc_service_cb::unbound</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>The endpoint unbound by the remote. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This callback is called when the endpoint binding is removed. It may happen on different reasons, e.g. when the remote deregistered the endpoint, connection was lost, or remote CPU got reset.</para>
<para>You may want to do some cleanup, resetting, e.t.c. and after that if you want to bound again, you can register the endpoint. When the remote becomes available again and it also registers the endpoint, the binding will be reestablished and the <computeroutput><ref refid="structipc__service__cb_1a76be12bf8a7964977b5d7512dd010110" kindref="member">bound()</ref></computeroutput> callback will be called.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">priv</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Private user data. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="zephyr/ipc/ipc_service.h" line="167" column="1" bodyfile="zephyr/ipc/ipc_service.h" bodystart="167" bodyend="-1"/>
